<div class="container">
        <h1 class="container__title">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h1>
        <div class="container__accordion">
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <input type="checkbox" checked>
                    <i></i>
                    <h2>How do I cook the dishes?</h2>
                    <p>All HOMEBAKE 425°:30™ products cook for 30 minutes at 425°F.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <input type="checkbox" checked>
                    <i></i>
                    <h2>Do I leave the film on when I cook it?</h2>
                    <p>Yes! Film should remain on the tray when it cooks in the oven. Remove film before serving.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <input type="checkbox" checked>
                    <i></i>
                    <h2>How should product be stored?</h2>
                    <p>All HOMEBAKE 425°:30™ products should be stored in the freezer.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <input type="checkbox" checked>
                    <i></i>
                    <h2>How many people does a tray serve?</h2>
                    <p>On average, each HOMEBAKE 425°:30™ has around 4 servings. You can find exact serving sizes for each product on the back of the packaging or on the product page.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <input type="checkbox" checked>
                    <i></i>
                    <h2>Can I store leftovers in the HOMEBAKE 425°:30™ trays?</h2>
                    <p>Yes! Cover your HOMEBAKE 425°:30™ trays and refrigerate to enjoy later!</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <input type="checkbox" checked>
                    <i></i>
                    <h2>Is HOMEBAKE 425°:30™ recyclable?</h2>
                    <p>Yes! Check the back of packaging for exact recycling instructions.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <!-- <div class="container__bottomBanner">
            <br>
        </div> -->
    </div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Faq section",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "section",
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Faq section"
    }
  ]
